@NODE Hardware "Hardware Requirements"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Wherefrom
@NEXT Software

                           HARDWARE REQUIREMENTS


You need an Amiga with 512 KByte (better 1 MByte or more), at least OS 2.x
and two disk drives or a harddisk.

MultiIndicator was coded on an Amiga 4000-040 with OS 3.0 and tested on:

    A4000-040 with  18 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1 and Picasso II
    A4000-040 with  10 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1
    A4000-040 with   6 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1
    A4000-030 with  10 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1
    A4000-030 with   6 MByte  OS 3.0 and OS 3.1
    A3000T    with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and Retina BLT Z3
    A3000T    with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1
    A3000     with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1 and Retina BLT Z3
    A3000     with  10 MByte  OS 2.0 and OS 3.1 and OmniBus graphics card
    A500+     with   1 MByte  OS 2.0
    A500      with 512 KByte  OS 2.0

@ENDNODE

@NODE Software "Software Requirements"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Hardware
@NEXT Installation

                           SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS


For the installation you need the Installer.

If you want to indicate XPK packed files you need the XPK-package. If you
also want to indicate powerpacked files you need also the
PowerPacker.library.

If you want to indicate Guide-files you need AmigaGuide or MultiView and the
AmigaGuide.library.

All these programs were not included in the MultiIndicator-archive, because
you can get the latest versions of these programs from every good mailbox or
from PD/FD-disks.

@ENDNODE

