@NODE Start "Start MultiIndicator"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Installation
@NEXT Help

                            START MULTIINDICATOR


MultiIndicator either can start from the Workbench or from the Shell.


          Workbench

            @{"with Icon" LINK Icon}
            @{"as DefaultTool" LINK DefTool}


          @{"Shell" LINK Shell}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Icon "Start from Workbench with Icon"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help

                       START FROM WORKBENCH WITH ICON

For starting MultiIndicator from icon, you have to click on the icon twice.
MultiIndicator creates an AppIcon after it was started. If you click this
AppIcon twice, an ASL-filerequester appears and you can select the file. If
you drag and drop another icon on the AppIcon, than the file or the direc-
tory to this icon will be displayed immediately.

    ToolTypes:

    If you want to change the ToolTypes, click the MultiIndicator icon and
    select the menuitem Information. Now change the ToolTypes and save it.


    Prefsfile=<path and name of the @{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}>
              (MultiIndicator will added the suffix .MIprefs if it wasn't
              specified and will search in the given path, ENVARC:MIndi-
              cator/ and ENV:MIndicator/.)

    IconX=<X-position of AppIcon>

    IconY=<Y-position of AppIcon>

@ENDNODE

@NODE DefTool "Start as DefaultTool"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help

                            START AS DEFAULTTOOL


If you want to use MultiIndicator as DefaultTool, than the program which
should be indicated must have a ProjectIcon. Click this ProjectIcon and
select the menuitem Information. The Iconwindow appears including the De-
fault Tool line in which you enter MI with complete path.

If the file Standard.MIprefs exists the fonts, screen, guideindicator and so
on were loaded from this file. If Standard.MIprefs doesn't exist, the inter-
nal settings were used.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Shell "Start from Shell"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Help

                              START FROM SHELL


If you start MultiIndicator from the Shell, you can load a @{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}.


    Syntax from the Shell:

    MI <File or Path> [-PREF <@{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}>]


        File          Name of the file to be viewed.

        Path          Name of the path that should be used for the ASL-
                      filerequester.

        -PREF         Tells MultiIndicator to load the specified @{"prefer-" LINK Menues}
                      @{"encefile" LINK Menues}.

        Prefsfile     Name and path of the @{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}. (MultiIndicator
                      will add the suffix .MIprefs if it wasn't specified
                      and will be search in the given path, ENVARC:MIndi-
                      cator/ and ENV:MIndicator/.)

        -PUB          Tells MultiIndicator to open the window on the named
                      Pubscreen.

        Pubscreen     Name of the Pubscreen.

        ?             Shows syntax.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Help "Help"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Start
@NEXT Menues

                                    HELP


Place the pointer about a menuitem or a gadget and press the helpbutton.

The file MI.help must available in the directory ENVARC:MIndicator/ or ENV:
MIndicator/. The InstallMI_?-Script or the Guide does this automatically.

@ENDNODE

