@NODE HEX-TFont "Menuitem HEX-Textfont..."
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                        THE MENUITEM HEX-TEXTFONT...


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.

Opens an ASL-fontrequester in which you can select the HEX-font for the
text. You may not select a proportional font.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Print "Menuitem Print... P"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                          THE MENUITEM PRINT... P


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

Opens the printer window, in which you can change printer options and start
the printaction.

    Variables for head- and footline:

        #f# = filename
        #d# = printdate
        #t# = printtime
        #p# = pagenumber

@ENDNODE

@NODE Clearmarker "MenuitemClear marker C"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                        THE MENUITEM CLEAR MARKER C


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

With this menuitem you can clear the markers.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Startmarker "Menuitem Startmarker 0"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                         THE MENUITEM STARTMARKER 0


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

With this menuitem you can set up the startmarker for the areaprintoption
(first visible line).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Endmarker "Menuitem Endmarker 1"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                          THE MENUITEM ENDMARKER 1


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

With this menuitem you can set up the endmarker for the areaprintoption
(last visible line).

@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC-Edit "Menuitem ASC-Edit... E"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                         THE MENUITEM ASC-EDIT... E


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

Starts the choosen ASC-editor with the parameters. The ASC-editor may not
detach, then the editing text will be shown.

Attention !!!

If it's a packed file you have to use an ASC-editor which is able to unpack
the file before editing it. Otherwise you only get strange characters.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX-Edit "Menuitem HEX-Edit... E"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                         THE MENUITEM HEX-EDIT... E


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an HEX-file.

Starts the choosen HEX-editor with the parameters. The HEX-editor may not
detach, then the editing text will be shown.

Attention!!!

If it's a packed file you have to use an HEX-editor which is able to unpack
the file before editing it.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Goto "Menuitem Goto... G"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                           THE MENUITEM GOTO... G


Opens the Goto window in which you can enter the line from where the text
would be shown.

@ENDNODE

@NODE ASC_HEX "Menuitem ASC » HEX"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                           THE MENUITEM ASC » HEX


This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

You can switch from the ASC-display to the HEX-display.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HEX_ASC "Menuitem HEX » ASC"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Gadgets

                           THE MENUITEM HEX » ASC

This menuitem is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file which
you have switched in HEX-mode.

You can switch from the HEX-display to the ASC-display.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Gadgets "Gadgets"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Menues
@NEXT Keyboard

                                  GADGETS


    MultiIndicator contains the following gadgets:

        ASC & HEX     @{"Textgadget 'Path/Filename'" LINK Text}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Buttongadget 'Search'" LINK Search}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Buttongadget 'Next'" LINK Next}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Buttongadget 'Previous'" LINK Previous}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Vertical Propgadget" LINK Vertical}
        ASC           @{"Horizontal Propgadget" LINK Horizontal}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Closegadget" LINK Close}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Zoomgadget" LINK Zoom}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Depthgadget" LINK Depth}
        ASC & HEX     @{"Sizegadget" LINK Size}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Text "Textgadget 'Path/Filename'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                       THE TEXTGADGET 'PATH/FILENAME'


Shows the name of the loaded file. If the name is too long, than the file-
name will be truncated.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Search "Buttongadget 'Search'" 
@TOC MAIN 
@PREV Gadgets 
@NEXT Keyboard

                         THE BUTTONGADGET 'SEARCH'


Opens the Searchwindow, in which you can enter the search word and change
another options. You can use the ? as a pattern.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Next "Buttongadget 'Next'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                          THE BUTTONGADGET 'NEXT'


Searches for the next item. If the next item was found, it will be marked.
If no item was found, a window appears which informs you.

This gadget is selectable if a searchword is inserted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Previous "Buttongadget 'Previous'"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                        THE BUTTONGADGET 'PREVIOUS'


Searches for the previous item. If the previous item was found, it will be
marked. If no item was found, a window appears which informs you.

This gadget is selectable if a searchword is inserted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Vertical "Propgadget vertical"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                          THE PROPGADGET VERTICAL


With this gadget you can scroll the text by the line (arrows), pages (click
below or above the scrollbar) or independent (click on the scrollbar and
move).

This works only if the text is longer than one screenpage.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Horizontal "Propgadget horizonal"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                         THE PROPGADGET HORIZONTAL


This gadget is only available if the selected file is an ASC-file.

With this gadget you can scroll the text by the letter (arrows), pages
(click left or right of the scrollbar) or independent (click on the
scrollbar and move).

This works only  if the text is wider than one screenpage.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Close "Closegadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                              THE CLOSEGADGET


With gadget has two meanings:

1. If MultiIndicator was started from Workbench, then only the window will
   be closed.

2. If MultiIndicator was started from Shell or as DefaultTool, then the
   window will be closed an the program terminates.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Zoom "Zoomgadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                             THE ZOOMGADGET


With this gadget you can choose between two windowsizes.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Depth "Depthgadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                             THE DEPTHGADGET


With this gadget you can toggle the window between foreground and back-
ground.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Size "Sizegadget"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Keyboard

                               THE SIZEGADGET


With this gadget you can reduce or enlarge the windowsize.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Keyboard "Keyboard"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT Mouse

                                  KEYBOARD


Window:

    ESC:                      If an other window as the mainwindow is
                              open, the window will be closed. Is only the
                              mainwindow is open, the mainwindow will be
                              closed and if MultiIndicator was started
                              from Shell or as DefaultTool the program
                              terminates.

StringGadgets:

    Tab:                      Next stringgadget activate
    Shift + Tab:              Previous stringgadget activate

Gadgets general:

    Underlined chars:         Activate the button or the stringgadget.
                              (Only if no stringgadget is activated.)

Textcontrol:

    Cursor up:                Line up
    Cursor down:              Line down
    Cursor left:              char left (only ASC-description)
    Cursor right:             char right (only ASC-description)
    Shift + Cursor...:        Page...
    Alt + Cursor...:          Goto textbegin -end
    Ctrl + Cursor...:         Goto textbegin -end
    Space:                    Page down

Numberblock:

    5:                        See ESC, but only the mainwindow
    Cursor up = 8:            Line up
    Cursor down = 2:          Line down
    Cursor left = 4:          char left (only ASC-description)
    Cursor right = 6:         char right (only ASC-description)
    Pg Up = 9:                Page up
    Pg Dn = 3:                Page down
    Home = 7:                 Goto textbegin
    End = 1:                  Goto textend

@ENDNODE

@NODE Mouse "Mouse"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Gadgets
@NEXT ARexx

                                   MOUSE


When you press and hold the left mousebutton while the pointer is in the
textwindow, you can scroll the text.


                                  ASC-mode

           +-------+-----------------------------------+-------+
           |       |                                   |       |
           |       |              FAST UP              |       |
           |       |                                   |       |
           |       +-----------------------------------+   R   |
           |   L   |                                   |       |
           |       |              SLOW UP              |   I   |
           |   E   |                                   |       |
           |       +-----------------------------------+   G   |
           |   F   |                                   |       |
           |       |             SLOW DOWN             |   H   |
           |   T   |                                   |       |
           |       +-----------------------------------+   T   |
           |       |                                   |       |
           |       |             FAST DOWN             |       |
           |       |                                   |       |
           +-------+-----------------------------------+-------+


                                  HEX-mode

           +---------------------------------------------------+
           |                                                   |
           |                      FAST UP                      |
           |                                                   |
           +---------------------------------------------------+
           |                                                   |
           |                      SLOW UP                      |
           |                                                   |
           +---------------------------------------------------+
           |                                                   |
           |                     SLOW DOWN                     |
           |                                                   |
           +---------------------------------------------------+
           |                                                   |
           |                     FAST DOWN                     |
           |                                                   |
           +---------------------------------------------------+

@ENDNODE

@NODE ARexx "ARexx"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Mouse
@NEXT Language

                                   AREXX


AppIcon:

    OPENFROMAPP File/A

        Opens the MultiIndicatorwindow and the file.


Mainwindow:

    ACTIVATE ,

        Activates the MutliIndicatorwindow.

    ALLTOFRONT ,

        Takes the screen and the MultiIndicatorwindow in front of all other.

    GOTOBYTE Byteoffset/A

        The file will be shown at the line in which the Byteoffset is and
        the first char will be marked.

    GOTOLINE Line/A

        The file will be shown at the given line.

    HIDETOAPP ,

        Closes the MultiIndicatorwindow. Only the AppIcon were shown. (Only
        available if MultiIndicator was started about the AppIcon.)

    LOAD Prefsfile/A

        Loads the Preferencefile.

    OPEN File/A

        Opens the file.

    QUIT ,

        Quit MultiIndicator.

    SCRTOBACK ,

        Takes the screen in the background.

    SCRTOFRONT ,

        Takes the screen in the foreground.

    SEARCH Searchword/A

        Serches for the searchword. (Put the $ char in front of the search-
        word if HEX-search will be useed.)

    WINTOBACK ,

        Takes the the MultiIndicatorwindow in the background.

    WINTOFRONT ,

        Takes the the MultiIndicatorwindow in the foreground.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Language "Language"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV ARexx
@NEXT History

                                  LANGUAGE


MultiIndicator supports the languages: English (intern), French (catalog)
Pascal Aubert, German (catalog), Italian (catalog) Marco Mellia, Spain
(catalog until 1.7)  Jose Garcia,  Swedish (catalog)  Mikael Silfver and
Johan Billing and Danish (catalog) Martin Rix.


Appeal:

I need the .ct-Files for the languages

Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish (>V1.7)

the .help-Files for the languages

French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish,

and the InstallMI_?-Script-Files for the languages

French, Italian, Norwegian, Dutch, Portuguese and Spanish.

For the .ct-File the File MI_?.cd is in the directory Catalogs.

If you make a .help-File, the text mustn't be longer than 16 lines and wider
than 50 chars.


Thanks in advance.

@ENDNODE

@NODE  History "History"
@TOC MAIN
@PREV Language
@NEXT Bugs

                                  HISTORY


****************************************************************************

03.08.93  V0.0   Programming begins.

****************************************************************************

12.08.93  V1.0   First public release.

****************************************************************************

16.08.93  V1.1   New loadroutine for ASC-text       -> considerably faster

                 New searchroutine for HEX and ASC  -> faster

                 New viewroutine for ASC-text -> depends on the new load-
                 routine

****************************************************************************

16.08.93  V1.11  Reworked Shell-parameters.

****************************************************************************

17.08.93  V1.12  ASC-HEX_View can used as DefaultTool.

****************************************************************************

18.08.93  V1.2   MultiIndicator opens an AppIcon if you start it from Work-
                 bench.

                 Support for ToolTypes.

****************************************************************************

18.08.93  V1.21  Now you can select in the Searchwindow if the search should
                 always start from the beginning and if the capitalization
                 should be taken into account.

****************************************************************************

18.08.93  V1.22  Now with textcontrol from the keyboard.

****************************************************************************

19.08.93  V1.23  Name of the program is now MultiIndicator.

                 Keyboardcontrol like CygnusEd implemented. (Boris 
                 Jakubaschk)

****************************************************************************

                 Second public release.

****************************************************************************

21.08.93  V1.3   MultiIndicator can indicate ESC-sequences and Tabs.

****************************************************************************

25.08.93  V1.4   XPK-Packer and PowerPacker support.

                 Infowindow available.

                 Buttongadgets change the look if you selct them. (Boris
                 Jakubaschk)

                 Keyboardcontrol changed. Alt -> Ctrl. (Boris Jakubaschk)

****************************************************************************

30.08.93  V1.5   Print option for ASC-Texts implement.

****************************************************************************

                 Third public release.

****************************************************************************

02.09.93  V1.5a  Spanish Catalog from José Garcia.

                 Catalogs now work under OS3.x.

                 Small bugs removed.

****************************************************************************

09.10.93  V1.6   NewLookMenues under OS3.x.

                 In gadgets you can use proportional fonts.

                 Window get a zoom gadget.

                 Print window reworked.

                 Variables in head- footline allowed.

                 The meaning of formfeed has changed!

                 Checkboxes and MXbuttons scaleable under OS3.x.

                 Graphicsbug in the pubscreenwindow under OS3.x removed.

                 Searchword will be indicated if it wasn't found.

                 One enforcerhit removed.

                 Text without end of line in the last line view exactely.

                 More than one packstep allowed.

                 Program can be terminated with ESC-button.

                 Waitpointer changed -> faster

                 If you start the program from the AppIcon, it remembers the
                 last path.

                 Help implemented.

                 Dynamic stack implemented. No stack is necessary, but no
                 control with mungwall possible.

                 Installer script added.

                 AmigaGuide manual added.

                 Swedish Catalog from Mikael Silfver.

                 New menuitem Open available. (Mikael Silfver)

                 Only the visible area of the screen used. (Jens Bönisch)

                 MI always remembers the last path.

                 For keyboardfetishists !

                 Windows (except password window and ASL-requester) can be
                 closed with ESC.

                 In the searchwindow you have to press return twice if the
                 stringgadget is activated and you want to start the search.

****************************************************************************

                 Fourth public release.

****************************************************************************

16.11.93  V1.7   Text in the password window is invisible.

                 In stringgadgets you can jump with cursor up and cursor
                 down.

                 Program optimized -> about 22% shorter.

                 A few internal improvements.

                 Now accessible via @{"E-Mail" LINK Author}.

                 Swedish Help-File from Mikael Silfver.

                 You can now use the Alt key instead of the Ctrl key.
                 (Mikael Silfver)

                 Publicscreen can now be select with a doubleclick. (Mikael
                 Silfver)

                 Small bugs removed. (Mikael Silfver)

                 MI now knows Hex-Code 9b resp. ASC-code 155. This is the
                 same as 'ESC['. (Is used in many BBSs)

****************************************************************************

                 Fifth public release.

****************************************************************************

12.01.94  V1.7   French Catalog from Pascal Aubert.

                 If the xpk????.librarys are be installed, the version will
                 be checked. (Not all !!! Sorry)

****************************************************************************

                 Sixth public release.

****************************************************************************

24.02.94  V1.8   You can switch an ASC-text from ASC-mode to HEX-mode and
                 back from HEX-mode to ASC-mode. (Michael Arlt)

                 You can set an ASC-textfont and a HEX-textfont. (Mikael
                 Silfver)

                 You can call an external editor if the text is a ASC-text.

                 You can scroll the text if you press and hold the left
                 mousebutton while the pointer is in the text-window.

                 You can choose the tabwidth. (Mikael Silfver)

                 You can save settings with Save and Save as and load
                 settings with Load.

                 Only one Shell-argument and three ToolTypes are available.

                 Shell: With -PREF <@{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}> you can load the
                 settings you wish.

                 ToolTypes: Prefsfile=<@{"preferencefile" LINK Menues}> same as Shell.

                 You can hand over printersettings without printing.

                 Formfeeds in the text will be removed.

                 In the Shell you can hand over a filename or pathname.

                 If you drop a drawer- or a diskicon on the MultiIndicator-
                 appicon the ASL-filerequester take with path.

                 If you start MultiIndicator from the AppIcon then you can
                 quit the program only if you choose the menuitem Quit.

                 Two enforcerhits removed.

                 Publicscreen Default added. So I hope the problems with
                 publicscreenmanagers are solved. Default means that the
                 MultiIndicatorwindow will be opend on the defaultpublic-
                 screen. (Adrian Demarais)

                 Installer, AmigaGuide, XPK and the PowerPacker.library are
                 removed, because the archive was too large.

                 Memory will be allocated with MEMF_ANY, so you can use
                 virtual memory.

                 Reworked english Help-File. (Johan Billing)

****************************************************************************

                 Seventh public release.

****************************************************************************

20.03.94  V1.8   Swedish Catalog and swedish Help-File become complete.
                 (Johan Billing)

****************************************************************************

                 AmiNET public release.

****************************************************************************

22.03.94  V1.8   Reworked english Document. (Johan Billing)

****************************************************************************

23.03.94  V1.81  If you start MultiIndicator from Shell and no filename or
                 directory will be hand over, then MultiIndicator use the
                 latest Shellpath. (Johan Billing)

                 When lines in ASC-texts ends with CR+LF or LF+CR, then
                 MultiIndicator replaces the CR+LF or LF+CR with CR. (Johan
                 Billing)

                 A "Sizegadget" at the bottom right corner implemented. This
                 Sizegadget isn't a normal Sizegadget, because you can only
                 choose, if you use full- or halfscreen. Is with enough ?
                 (Bill Bennett)

                 Searchroutine improved -> up to 20% faster.

****************************************************************************

03.04.94  V1.82  The spacing between the lines in ASC- and HEX-mode can now
                 be changed.

                 Publicscreenbug removed.

                 Zoomgadgetbug removed.

****************************************************************************

                 Eighth public release.

****************************************************************************

03.05.94  V1.85  A little ARexxPort implemented.

                 Texts with more than 100 ESC-sequences in one line were
                 shown correctly.

                 Current line and whole lines were shown.

                 New menuitem Goto implemented.

                 Italian Catalog from Marco Mellia.

****************************************************************************

                 Ninth public release.

****************************************************************************

20.07.94  V1.9   You can call an external HEX-editor.

                 New ARexx-command GOTOBYTE.

                 Searchpattern ? implemented.

                 ALLTOBACK will be replaced by SCRTOBACK and WINTOBACK.

                 Page down with the space key. (Marco Mellia)

****************************************************************************

                 Tenth public release.
                 AmiNET public release.

****************************************************************************

28.08.94  V2.0   You can now scroll left and right with the mouse.

                 If you would search for $ in the HEX-mode, you have to
                 enter $$.

                 The window ist full resizeable. (Bill Bennett and Michael
                 Arlt)

                 You can select an area to print.

                 3 windowsizes are available: maximum screensize, visible
                 screenarea and current windowsize. (Michael Arlt)

                 Das MultiIndicatorwindow is now an AppWindow. (Michael
                 Arlt)

                 MultiIndicator is SysIHack-compatibel :-)

                 2 new ARexx-commands SCRTOFRONT und WINTOFRONT.

                 ARexx-command GOTOBYTE have chanced a little.

                 Guides rewrite.

                 Docs included.

                 An additional MultiIndicatorversion without dynamic stack
                 included. So you can test MultiIndicator with MungWall.
                 Attention: This Version needs a stack of 8192 Bytes !

                 New E-Mail-Address !!! (fatso@turtle.insider.sub.de)

****************************************************************************

                 Eleventh public release.
                 AmiNET public release.

****************************************************************************
11.09.94  V2.1   MultiIndicator can quit with the  5-key from the number-
                 block.

                 No Problems with more MultiIndicators and packed Guides.

****************************************************************************

                 Twelfth public release.

****************************************************************************

26.09.94  V2.2   ASC-chars < 32 in Guide-files allowed. (Bruno Jansen)

                 After loading a file the AppIcon disappears and it  appears
                 only the file was closed. (Bruno Jansen)

****************************************************************************

                 Thirteenth public release.

****************************************************************************

13.11.94  V2.3   -PUB Keyword implemented again. (Bernd Grunwald)

                 Danish  Catalog,  Help-File  and  Installscript from Martin
                 Rix.

****************************************************************************

                 Fourteenth public release.

****************************************************************************

